==English==

{{rank|comes|stand|past|502|suppose|else|entered|none}}

===Etymology===
{{F.}} ''supposer''; prefix ''sub-'' under + ''poser'' to place; - corresponding in meaning to {{L.}} ''supponere'', ''suppositum'', to put under, to substitute, falsify, counterfeit. See [[pose]].

===Verb===
'''to suppose'''   ([[supposed]], [[supposing]])

[[Transitive]]:
#to take for granted; to conclude, with less than absolute supporting data; to [[believe]].
#to theorize or hypothesize

